  "description": "Growing protocol for *Lactuca sativa*, optimized for cool-season production and succession sowing. Seed germinates at 10–20°C but exhibits thermoinhibition above 25°C. Succession-sow every 2–3 weeks for continuous harvest; cut-and-come-again harvesting extends production. 25–55 days to maturity depending on type and temperature.",
